The appointed Prime Minister, Mario Monty, will meet with the President of Italy tomorrow to present a new Government that will face the crisis that has put the country at the brink of an economic disaster.
The appointed Italian Prime Minister, Mario Monti, will meet with the President of Italy on Wednesday to present a new Government that will face a crisis that has put Italy at the brink of an economic disaster and has damaged the entire eurozone.
A presidential statement stated that Monty, appointed on Sunday, would meet with President George Napolitano on Wednesday to confirm that he could form a government.
