Monty said he would present to the President the results of his talks with political parties in his attempt to form a government.
“I want to reaffirm my full confidence in our country's ability to get out of this difficult period,” said the former European Commissioner to reporters.
Monty did not say directly that he had been able to form a government, but a tone of his comments showed that the obstacles had been overcome.
