What did you plan to do in Costa Rica?
Since we've never played there before, we don't have any restrictions on what we can do.
We're going to try to make the best show of all kinds of songs possible; we're going to try to play a few songs from each album and present our fans with a wide variety of repertoires.
You never repeat the repertoire.
How do you do that?
I think it's partly because we have nine records and we can play more than 120 songs, and everyone likes different songs, so it's hard to choose what songs to play every night.
When we have two or three songs that we haven't played for a while, it keeps us in tune and surprises us because it reminds us of the reasons why we loved those songs and what we could forget.
