We're good friends with the guys from Soundgarden, Mudhoney and Alice in Chains.
It's great when the movement grows up from a group of friends, and that's unusual.
From time to time, one group from one city appears, but it is far more strange when five or ten groups appear in one city at a time.
We are proud to be part of a Seattle group.
I still play with some of them from time to time.
Last year we were at a festival with Alice in Chains and we were in Canada with Mudhoney, we saw Soundgarden during their tour, so we're happy to be friends with all of them and it's an honor for us to be part of Seattle's sound.
It's also very strange that your group has stayed together for such a long time.
