How do you remember your other project, Manother Love Bone?
I think we're writing really good songs, and it was great at first.
We've been a group for almost three years, and we haven't released any albums until Andy ( Andrew Woods) died.
It was a lot of disappointment because it took so long, and most importantly, we're still close friends with Bruce (Ferweser) and Greg (Gilmore) who started with us in the group, and when I hear a song or see a photograph, I think about the amazing person that Andy was, and how he made me laugh, it was always a pleasure to go to work, laugh, talk about music and football and a lot of other things.
