He transferred four surgeries to the cancer of the tongue, lost 18 kilograms of weight, adding other diseases, such as severe erosion gastritis, gastric cysts, kidney stones, high blood pressure, and problems with leg circulation, the doctor listed.
Fuhimori has been in prison since September 2007, in the Police National Office of Special Operations.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the army's destruction squad, which operated secretly in the first years of his reign.
